# Implementation checklist (125.md)

Use this checklist when implementing or reviewing the Sprint 2 chatbot. Tick items as done.

**Focus:** Domain-focused chatbot with advanced RAG + tool calling using Next.js and LangChain.

## Setup

- [x] Node on LTS (if needed)
- [x] pnpm installed; use it for this project
- [x] Next.js app created in current project folder
- [x] Required dependencies installed (LangChain, OpenAI SDK, validation libs, vector DB libs)
- [x] OpenAI API key obtained and stored securely (`.env.local`, never in code)

## Domain definition

- [x] Domain/use case selected and documented (clear scope)
- [x] Knowledge sources selected and added to `data/` (hair-salon KB placeholders + extracted pricing)
- [ ] Domain-specific system prompt and safety guardrails defined

## Core requirements (125.md)

### 1) RAG implementation

- [x] Knowledge base ingestion pipeline implemented
- [x] Chunking strategy configured and documented
- [x] Embeddings-based retrieval implemented
- [x] Similarity search working with relevant top-k retrieval
- [ ] Query translation/rewriting step implemented for better retrieval
- [x] Response includes source context/citations where possible

### 2) Tool calling

- [ ] At least 3 domain-relevant tools implemented
- [ ] Tool input schemas validated (e.g. `zod`)
- [ ] Tool-call errors handled gracefully
- [ ] Tool results rendered clearly in the UI

### 3) Domain specialization

- [x] Chatbot behavior is clearly specialized to chosen domain
- [x] Domain-focused knowledge base integrated into responses
- [x] Domain-specific safety/security considerations applied

### 4) Technical implementation

- [ ] LangChain integration implemented for model + retrieval workflow
- [x] API route validation and sanitization implemented
- [x] Proper error handling added (typed, safe responses)
- [ ] Logging/monitoring added (without leaking secrets)
- [x] Rate limiting added for chat endpoint
- [x] API key management follows secure env-var practices

### 5) User interface

- [x] Intuitive chat interface implemented in Next.js (UI skeleton + responsive layout)
- [x] Sources/citations displayed in responses (mocked UI blocks, TODO wired to backend later)
- [x] Tool-call outputs displayed in dedicated UI area (mocked UI blocks, TODO wired to backend later)
- [x] Progress/loading indicators shown for long operations (mocked UI states for long operations)

